The World Health Organization says every year hundreds of millions of people
are becoming ill with preventable chronic respiratory diseases.  
One of the most common allergies is said to be hay fever, which is caused by
contact with ragweed [Botanical name: artemisiifolia]. Scientists now say the
increase in ragweed is stimulated by climate change.  VOA's Melinda Smith has
more on this condition.
 
 
 
 
